## Next Steps for Deployment

To complete the Vercel Web Analytics setup, the following steps should be performed in the Vercel Dashboard:

1. **Enable Web Analytics**:
   - Navigate to the [Vercel Dashboard](https://vercel.com/dashboard)
   - Select the `MARGAN_DAS` project
   - Click the **Analytics** tab
   - Click **Enable** to activate Web Analytics
   - This will add new routes scoped at `/_vercel/insights/*` after the next deployment

2. **Deploy the Application**:
   ```bash
   vercel deploy
   ```
   Or push to the connected Git repository (recommended for automated deployments)

3. **Verify Tracking** (after deployment):
   - Visit the deployed site
   - Open browser's Developer Tools → Network tab
   - Navigate to any page
   - Look for Fetch/XHR requests to `/_vercel/insights/view`
   - Presence of these requests confirms tracking is active

4. **View Analytics Data**:
   - Go to Vercel Dashboard → Project → Analytics tab
   - Data will start appearing within minutes of receiving traffic
   - After a few days, explore data using filtering panels
   - Pro and Enterprise plans can add custom events for detailed tracking

## Technical Notes

### Route Support
- This plain React implementation does not have automatic route support
- If the project implements client-side routing (e.g., React Router) in the future, consider:
  - The Analytics component will still track page views through browser's Navigation API
  - For better route tracking, custom events can be implemented

### Privacy & Compliance
- Vercel Web Analytics is privacy-friendly and GDPR-compliant
- No cookies are used for tracking
- No personal data is collected
- Learn more: [Vercel Analytics Privacy Policy](https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/privacy-policy)

### Performance Impact
- The Analytics script loads asynchronously (doesn't block page rendering)
- Minimal bundle size impact (~2-3KB gzipped)
- No impact on Core Web Vitals or page load performance

